<Link id="l00054" /><CodeLine lineNumber="54"><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">namespace </span><span class="doxyHighlight"><a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm">llvm</a> &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00055" /><CodeLine lineNumber="55"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00056" /><CodeLine lineNumber="56"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// A temporary struct to spill SGPRs.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00057" /><CodeLine lineNumber="57"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// This is mostly to spill SGPRs to memory. Spilling SGPRs into VGPR lanes emits</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00058" /><CodeLine lineNumber="58"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// just v&#95;writelane and v&#95;readlane.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00059" /><CodeLine lineNumber="59"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00060" /><CodeLine lineNumber="60"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// When spilling to memory, the SGPRs are written into VGPR lanes and the VGPR</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00061" /><CodeLine lineNumber="61"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// is saved to scratch (or the other way around for loads).</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00062" /><CodeLine lineNumber="62"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// For this, a VGPR is required where the needed lanes can be clobbered. The</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00063" /><CodeLine lineNumber="63"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// RegScavenger can provide a VGPR where currently active lanes can be</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00064" /><CodeLine lineNumber="64"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// clobbered, but we still need to save inactive lanes.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00065" /><CodeLine lineNumber="65"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// The high-level steps are:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00066" /><CodeLine lineNumber="66"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// - Try to scavenge SGPR(s) to save exec</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00067" /><CodeLine lineNumber="67"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// - Try to scavenge VGPR</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00068" /><CodeLine lineNumber="68"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// - Save needed, all or inactive lanes of a TmpVGPR</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00069" /><CodeLine lineNumber="69"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// - Spill/Restore SGPRs using TmpVGPR</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00070" /><CodeLine lineNumber="70"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// - Restore TmpVGPR</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00071" /><CodeLine lineNumber="71"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00072" /><CodeLine lineNumber="72"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// To save all lanes of TmpVGPR, exec needs to be saved and modified. If we</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00073" /><CodeLine lineNumber="73"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// cannot scavenge temporary SGPRs to save exec, we use the following code:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00074" /><CodeLine lineNumber="74"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// buffer&#95;store&#95;dword TmpVGPR ; only if active lanes need to be saved</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00075" /><CodeLine lineNumber="75"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// s&#95;not exec, exec</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00076" /><CodeLine lineNumber="76"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// buffer&#95;store&#95;dword TmpVGPR ; save inactive lanes</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00077" /><CodeLine lineNumber="77"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// s&#95;not exec, exec</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00078" /><CodeLine lineNumber="78" lineLink="/docs/api/structs/llvm/sgprspillbuilder"><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">struct </span><span class="doxyHighlight"><a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/sgprspillbuilder/#a35d6d8a3367d6ef42ec184b84213ea52">SGPRSpillBuilder</a> &#123;</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00158" /><CodeLine lineNumber="158"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Tries to scavenge SGPRs to save EXEC and a VGPR. Uses v0 if no VGPR is</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00159" /><CodeLine lineNumber="159"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// free.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00160" /><CodeLine lineNumber="160"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Writes these instructions if an SGPR can be scavenged:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00161" /><CodeLine lineNumber="161"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// s&#95;mov&#95;b64 s&#91;6:7&#93;, exec   ; Save exec</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00162" /><CodeLine lineNumber="162"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// s&#95;mov&#95;b64 exec, 3        ; Wanted lanemask</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00163" /><CodeLine lineNumber="163"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// buffer&#95;store&#95;dword v1    ; Write scavenged VGPR to emergency slot</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00164" /><CodeLine lineNumber="164"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00165" /><CodeLine lineNumber="165"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Writes these instructions if no SGPR can be scavenged:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00166" /><CodeLine lineNumber="166"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// buffer&#95;store&#95;dword v0    ; Only if no free VGPR was found</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00167" /><CodeLine lineNumber="167"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// s&#95;not&#95;b64 exec, exec</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00168" /><CodeLine lineNumber="168"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// buffer&#95;store&#95;dword v0    ; Save inactive lanes</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00169" /><CodeLine lineNumber="169"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//                          ; exec stays inverted, it is flipped back in</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00170" /><CodeLine lineNumber="170"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//                          ; restore.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00171" /><CodeLine lineNumber="171" lineLink="/docs/api/structs/llvm/sgprspillbuilder/#ac7c906625fab2baf872e16248962b859"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">void</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/sgprspillbuilder/#ac7c906625fab2baf872e16248962b859">prepare</a>() &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00172" /><CodeLine lineNumber="172"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Scavenged temporary VGPR to use. It must be scavenged once for any number</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00173" /><CodeLine lineNumber="173"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// of spilled subregs.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00174" /><CodeLine lineNumber="174"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// FIXME: The liveness analysis is limited and does not tell if a register</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00175" /><CodeLine lineNumber="175"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// is in use in lanes that are currently inactive. We can never be sure if</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00176" /><CodeLine lineNumber="176"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// a register as actually in use in another lane, so we need to save all</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00578" /><CodeLine lineNumber="578"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00579" /><CodeLine lineNumber="579"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// On GFX90A, the number of VGPRs and AGPRs need not be equal. Theoretically,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00580" /><CodeLine lineNumber="580"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// a wave may have up to 512 total vector registers combining together both</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00581" /><CodeLine lineNumber="581"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// VGPRs and AGPRs. Hence, in an entry function without calls and without</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00583" /><CodeLine lineNumber="583"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// budget for VGPRs.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00584" /><CodeLine lineNumber="584"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00585" /><CodeLine lineNumber="585"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// TODO: it shall be possible to estimate maximum AGPR/VGPR pressure and split</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00586" /><CodeLine lineNumber="586"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//       register file accordingly.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00587" /><CodeLine lineNumber="587"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">if</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (ST.hasGFX90AInsts()) &#123;</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00589" /><CodeLine lineNumber="589"><span class="doxyHighlight">      MaxNumVGPRs /= 2;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00590" /><CodeLine lineNumber="590"><span class="doxyHighlight">      MaxNumAGPRs = MaxNumVGPRs;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00591" /><CodeLine lineNumber="591"><span class="doxyHighlight">    &#125; </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">else</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00592" /><CodeLine lineNumber="592"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">if</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (MaxNumVGPRs &gt; TotalNumVGPRs) &#123;</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00597" /><CodeLine lineNumber="597"><span class="doxyHighlight">    &#125;</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l01887" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1887"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// register was assigned for return value ABI lowering with a COPY</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01888" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1888"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// instruction. As given below, with the epilog reload, the earlier COPY</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01889" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1889"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// appeared to be dead during machine-cp.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01890" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1890"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// ...</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01891" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1891"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// v0 in WWM operation, needs the WWM spill at prolog/epilog.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01892" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1892"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// $vgpr0 = V&#95;WRITELANE&#95;B32 $sgpr20, 0, $vgpr0</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01893" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1893"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// ...</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01894" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1894"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Epilog block:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01895" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1895"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// $vgpr0 = COPY $vgpr1 // outgoing value moved to v0</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01896" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1896"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// ...</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01897" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1897"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// WWM spill restore to preserve the inactive lanes of v0.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01898" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1898"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// $sgpr4&#95;sgpr5 = S&#95;XOR&#95;SAVEEXEC&#95;B64 -1</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01899" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1899"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// $vgpr0 = BUFFER&#95;LOAD $sgpr0&#95;sgpr1&#95;sgpr2&#95;sgpr3, $sgpr32, 0, 0, 0</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01900" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1900"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// $exec = S&#95;MOV&#95;B64 killed $sgpr4&#95;sgpr5</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01901" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1901"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// ...</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01902" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1902"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// SI&#95;RETURN implicit $vgpr0</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01903" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1903"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// ...</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01904" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1904"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// To fix it, mark the same reg as a tied op for such restore instructions</span></CodeLine>
